oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Memphis Singer Presley Signed by RCA-Victor
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: "Memphis Singer Presley Signed by RCA-Victor for Recording Work" article appearing in the Memphis Press Scimitar

Elvis Presley (1935-1977) was an American singer and actor, dubbed the "King of Rock and Roll." He is regarded as one of the most significant cultural icons, as well as one of the most celebrated and influential musicians of the 20th century. Discovered by Sam Phillips at Sun Records in 1954, Presley spent over two decades under contract to the RCA-Victor record label.
